{
  "id": "myth-char-89fb97a2c3ca",
  "name": "Sefa Rocksquill",
  "type": "pc",
  "status": "active",
  "description": "A Vael lance of the Lanternfall Warden draft - hugely built for a kestrel-kin, wingspear and target shield, leather harness. Hits like an Ossuin; constitution of a songbird.",
  "narrative": "Sefa Rocksquill was born to the Moult but never fit it: too big for the courier-rafts, too slow for the lane-races, a kestrel built like a lanner falcon. The deed-name came young - feathers so heavy-quilled the riggers joked she was part spire-rock - and she carried it to the one place in the sky where heavy is a qualification: the Gale Wardens' lances. She fights with wingspear and shield in the dive-and-pass style of the Lanternfall draft. Her constitution has always been her secret weakness (CON 6, Healing Rate 1): she does not get sick often, but when she is hurt, she stays hurt, and she has learned to fight accordingly - end it fast, never trade blows. She hates the Stilling the way sailors hate the doldrums that starve them: the Moult lost two lanes and a cousin-raft to dead air in her lifetime. The draft is the family the flotilla never quite was.",
